name: ArrowHead
shortdesc: The shape of one or both ends of an open path.

property.name: SIMPLE_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: An arrow head formed by two slanting lines whose intersection forms a 45-degree angle and whose stroke weight is the same as the path's stroke.

property.name: SIMPLE_WIDE_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: An arrow head formed by two slanting lines whose intersection forms a 90-degree angle and whose stroke weight is the same as the path's stroke.

property.name: TRIANGLE_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A solid triangle arrow head whose point describes a 45-degree angle.

property.name: TRIANGLE_WIDE_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A solid triangle arrow head whose point describes a 90-degree angle.

property.name: BARBED_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A solid arrow head whose pierced end bows sharply toward the point and whose point describes a 45-degree angle.

property.name: CURVED_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A solid arrow head whose pierced end concaves toward the point and whose point describes a 45-degree angle.

property.name: CIRCLE_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A hollow circle whose outline is the same weight as the stroke. The circle's diameter is 5 times the stroke width.

property.name: CIRCLE_SOLID_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A solid circle whose diameter is 5 times the stroke width.

property.name: SQUARE_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A hollow square set perpendicular to the path, whose outline is the same weight as the stroke. The length of one side of the square is 5 times the stroke width.

property.name: SQUARE_SOLID_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A solid square set perpendicular to the end of the path. The length of one side of the square is 5 times the stroke width.

property.name: BAR_ARROW_HEAD
property.shortdesc: A vertical bar bisected by the stroke, which meets the stroke at a right angle and is the same weight as the stroke. The bar's length is 4.5 times the stroke width.
